@subsubheading Notes:

@itemize --
@item @command{canenable(9)} is really an @cite{SVR 3.2} compatibility function that should not be
used with @cite{SVR 4} @dfn{STREAMS} programs.

@item For the most part, the @cite{UNIX System V Release 4.0 STREAMS} functions are universally
implemented.  Exceptions to this include @command{backq(9)}, which appears to be an oversight on the
part of @cite{SUPER-UX} documentation; @command{esbbcall(9)}, that can be emulated by calling
@command{bufcall(9)} with a size of zero; @command{getadmin(9)}, @command{getmid(9)} and
@command{strlog(9)}, which seems to be more of a @cite{Solaris} and @cite{LiS} problem;
@command{SAMESTR(9)}, which is only useful on systems with @dfn{STREAMS} support for pipes and
FIFOs.

@item @cite{LiS} always misses what @cite{Solaris} misses.  That is probably not a coincidence.

@item For specific compatibility notes, see the individual manual pages for these functions.
@end itemize

Because all of these functions are supported by the core @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS} package, and all
but @command{getadmin(9)}, @command{getmid(9)} and @command{strlog(9)} are supported by the core
@cite{Linux STREAMS (LiS)} package, these functions are not provided in the @cite{SVR 4.2
Compatibility Module}, @file{streams_svr4compat.ko}.  The three functions missing from @cite{LiS}
are implemented in the @cite{Linux Fast-STREAMS Compatibility Module}, @file{streams_lfscompat.ko},
that is only built and installed against @cite{LiS}.

