@item @command{MPSTR_STPRELE(9)} @tab -- unlock a STREAMS stream head from exclusive access
@end multitable

@subsubheading Notes:

@itemize --
@item Although they are @dfn{STREAMS} functions, nobody other than @cite{UnixWare} mentions the
@command{MPSTR_*} functions, so they are placed in the @cite{SVR 4.2 MP} compatibility module,
@file{streams_svr4compat}.

@item The @command{pcmsg(9)} function seems to have been missed by a number of implementations.

@item @cite{LiS} always misses what @cite{Solaris} misses.  That is probably not a coincidence.

@item @cite{Lis} did not have anything resembling a proper @command{qprocson(9)} or
@command{qprocsoff(9)} implementation until recently.  @cite{LiS} did not have any
@command{freezestr(9)} or @command{unfreezestr(9)} implementation until recently.  Neither
implementations are fully functional or in accordance with @dfn{STREAMS} documentation, making them
almost unusable.

@item @cite{AIX}, @cite{OSF/1} and @cite{UXP/V} do not document any of these functions, which is
bad: these are the MP functions for @dfn{STREAMS}.
@end itemize

